 <text>
  <front>
   <head>To LOVE: written extempore.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">power, ah! wherefore reign,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Alone among the rural train,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Is it because you seldom find,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The giddy throng to truth inclin'd.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ah! wherefore in the modish breast,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Art thou so rarely found a guest,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Must fashion occupy thy place,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And custom, hymens charms efface.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Alas! how few are born to prove,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The joys of undissembled love,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">How few can boast a gen'rous flame,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Inspir'd by virtue's sacred name.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Is it because thou'rt partial grown,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And yield to beauties power alone,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Must merit plead her right in vain,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And mourn for truth's unpity'd pain.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In vain is every grace combin'd,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To elevate the youthful mind,</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">If nature joins not to disclose,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The lilly and the blushing rose.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ye youths of this licentious age,</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">No more in idle cares engage,</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">No longer artful scenes pursue,</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But grant to merit — all its due.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
